item.description:
No energy transition in the past Still true, far more coal is used now than in the 19th cent, there has never been an energy &ldquo;transition&rdquo; as such, only energy additions. From:
biomass → biomass + coal → biomass + coal + oil → biomass + coal + oil + natural gas &hellip;
Oil and comfort No u won&rsquo;t find oil in any random place, no technology cannot create oil (in ground anyways, u can do coal to oil at a cost), most important keeping u comfortable in future isn&rsquo;t AI but oil, gas, &amp; coal
